  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The pump is deployed in continuous in vivo duty across extended perfusion procedures (up to 6 hours), where bearing wear, seal degradation, and motor driver voltage transients are recognized operational realities. All model and validation activities assume nominal hardware throughout; no fault states are represented.",
